list_ex_of_english: Fifty per cent of drivers have admitted falling asleep at the wheel.

Though the only movement, the words correspond to the visual suggestion of a different temporality by describing the act of falling asleep, a move into dream-time.
She was averse to being house-trained, she was a thief, and spent much of her time asleep in our best armchair.
I swear the driver was half asleep.
Older people awaken more frequently but fall back asleep at the same rate as younger people.
Only one of these was a case aggravated by the fact that the victim was asleep.
